The daily AI news show is expanding beyond GitHub updates with a new AI aggregator that collects content from multiple sources across the ecosystem. This aims to improve the quality and relevance of daily update videos.

Tokenomics updates are 75% complete, covering areas such as tributes, AI KOL/memecoin trading, retro funding, AI investing via a game show, and an agent marketplace. The team is actively developing these features while iterating in real-time.
Development updates include AI trading agents making profits, a new liquidity provider for DAO AUM tokens, an AI investment game show, and the launch of RPGF for Eliza contributors.
The NYSE floor has become a symbolic monument as algorithms have taken over trading since the mid-2000s. Now, AI models with autonomous trading capabilities provide 24/7 access to capital markets.
Eliza has been in development for years, and now is a unique moment where open-source hackers, DAOists, AI researchers, and crypto enthusiasts are collaborating to solve coordination challenges.
China is aggressively investing in AI to dominate the global race, with expectations of significant government funding, corporate espionage, and industry drama.

Deepseek R1 LLM, an open-source AI model competing with OpenAI's O1, may have origins in a Chinese crypto mining and high-frequency trading firm, highlighting the intersection of AI, crypto, and open-source development.
Eliza now includes a fact-checking feature for posts, allowing users to verify information in real-time.
A major update is coming, featuring multiple significant changes, including AI Shark Tank, which is expected to be a game-changer.

Eliza is gaining intelligent email automation, allowing it to evaluate conversations, detect key topics, and send contextual emails automatically. The feature is still a work in progress but is functional.
A new plugin integrates Samsung SmartThings with Eliza, expanding its smart home capabilities.

Eliza now integrates with BitMind's API via a new plugin, enabling AI-generated image detection and analysis. The system provides confidence scoring, memory management, and historical analysis tracking.
Edriziai, an AI-powered startup mentor assistant, has been introduced. Integrated with Slack, it provides guidance on startup fundamentals, financial planning, mental health, fundraising, and more.

categories.title: Bug Fixes and Issues in ElizaOS

content.text: A bug in the RAG knowledge system caused incorrect re-indexing of knowledge on startup due to mismatched ID formats. The issue was fixed by ensuring scoped IDs are properly used when checking for existing knowledge.
An error in the Twitter client prevented fetching parent tweets while building conversation threads. The issue occurred despite the parent tweet existing at the time of the request.
A user reported difficulty in creating a hardcoded response for a Twitter agent. Despite following an example from the weather plugin, the agent's response did not match the expected hardcoded text.

The `plugins` field in `character.json` appears to be unusable, as plugins are instead created based on environment variables in `AgentRuntime`. Users expect plugins from `character.json` to be initialized independently.

Inefficient vector similarity search in memory cache led to duplicate API calls when using `plugin-coinmarketcap` to check crypto prices. The system failed to reuse similar memories, causing redundant database entries.

categories.title: AI Agents: The New Websites and Their Expanding Capabilities

content.text: The rise of AI agents is being compared to the early days of the internet in 1995, where websites were the primary innovation. Now, AI agents are emerging as the new digital frontier.

AI trading agents are becoming more sophisticated. @degenspartanai is currently trading based on insights from Crypto Twitter (CT) and will soon integrate a filtering mechanism for better token selection. Meanwhile, @aixvc_agent operates by leveraging recommendations from a closed group of skilled traders. Additionally, there are plans for a new show where AI agents will participate in a 'Shark Tank'-style event.

A new Sei Plugin has been introduced to enhance AI agents' capabilities on the Sei Network. This plugin allows ELIZA agents to interact with the Sei blockchain, initially supporting fund transfers. The update includes unit tests, manual testing, and documentation to ensure smooth integration. The plugin does not affect the core functionality of the agents but expands their ability to operate within the Sei ecosystem.

categories.title: Recent Updates in ElizaOS: Bug Fixes and New Plugin Integrations

content.text: A bug fix was implemented in the RAG Knowledge system to ensure scoped IDs are correctly used when checking for existing knowledge. Previously, there was a mismatch in how knowledge IDs were generated and verified, leading to inconsistencies in knowledge retrieval. The fix ensures that the same ID generation method is used in both checking and storing knowledge entries.

A new Hyperbolic Plugin was introduced for managing GPU instances on the Hyperbolic platform through ElizaOS. This plugin allows users to list available GPUs, check account balances, monitor GPU statuses, view spending history, rent GPU instances, and terminate them. The implementation includes comprehensive error handling, logging, and API request validation.

Support for the Mina blockchain was added to ElizaOS through a new plugin. Mina is a lightweight layer-1 blockchain with zero-knowledge smart contracts. The plugin enables token operations and wallet management, integrating with ElizaOS's existing infrastructure. Documentation and testing steps were provided to ensure smooth deployment and usage.
